##30 hours from the United States to Shanghai to experience the three major international airports, Shanghai Yan out of the truth

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

The positive change in China's epidemic today is the result of extensive travel restrictions over the past few weeks, and the selfless dedication of the angels in White, in stark contrast to the rest of the world.

By Li Ying

After staying in the US for more than 40 days due to the epidemic, I finally started my journey from San Francisco to Shanghai in the early morning of March 9. Due to the cancellation of the direct flight between China and the US, I had to transfer to Hong Kong, after 30 hours in three international cities, experience a different countries and regions in response to the new crown epidemic control measures and human warmth.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
San Francisco Airport

It was 9 p.m. from San Francisco, the highways were clear, the airports were orderly, and the guards were watching the faces of the people who came and went, as if wearing masks wasn't the point of their attention, and no one was getting shot in the forehead. Discreet face masks, protective glasses are worn, but a little out of place in the security line. The sales clerk in the duty-free shop asked the passer-by through the mask if he needed any help and was very enthusiastic. Coach, who politely introduced the season's new line, said the masks were issued at the airport, one for each person, with or without their choice, while 90 percent of the Asian faces in the store wore masks and about 30 percent of other skin tones, mostly middle aged and elderly. In the departure lounge, airline staff are asking pre-boarding passengers whether they have completed the Hong Kong entry health declaration form and whether they have visited any of the key affected countries. Cathay Pacific Staff Member Luke said that the airline has advice on epidemic prevention, do Not Force to wear a mask, but if you wear a blue mask must be medical, the other can not, so the service staff wear masks very few. Only 30% of the seats on the plane, half of the people wearing masks, we consciously sit apart.

After more than 15 hours of lying down and sleeping, I arrived at Hong Kong International Airport at 7 a.m. , got off the plane quickly and easily, was not required to take a temperature, and passengers from all countries in the Transit Zone wore masks and sat around consciously. After 10 o'clock, the store gradually opened, the store was quiet, the shop staff were wearing masks standing at the door to canvass customers, BURBERRY, Gucci, IWC door empty, as soon as someone entered the store will be informed of a discount, many stores also advertise that airport personnel can get a 70% discount. When I went to the restaurant area on the top floor at lunchtime, I saw that everything was empty. There was no need to wait in line at Zhengdou, Meixin and Cuiyuan, which had been doing good business. The lady who collected the dishes told me that the number of flights to and from Hong Kong had been greatly reduced since the beginning of the epidemic, many, many fewer people, now most of the meal is the airport staff, they are required to wear masks and gloves service, but most of the time there is nothing to do. Important notices have been broadcast reminding Hong Kong people not to travel to Hubei in the near future. A meal of 120 Yuan Ramen on the documentary "boiling bar, Hot pot" hot stomach, homesick.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The airport is deserted

After 2 pm, the boarding information finally came out, slowly moved past, found that there are many people waiting for the plane, judging from the color of skin, accent, the United States, Europe, Shanghai, Beijing, Zhejiang Min, everyone wearing masks, someone else was wearing latex gloves. When it was time to board the plane, there was a long queue. Airline staff asked passengers one by one if they were from "key areas" . After the boarding cards were marked, they were allowed to board the plane. More than 90% of the seats were filled, which scared me into not taking off my mask for the whole flight, and the cabin service also changed from the choice of meals in the past to the issuance of snack bags, service staff and passengers basic no contact.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Pudong airport at last

Arrived Pudong Airport is 6:00 pm, the plane stopped after the captain told everyone not to move, to wait for the customs up to take the temperature of the guests. After 40 minutes, the first group of 20 people, most of them foreigners, were called off the plane? Would it be dangerous to spend just over two hours with them in an airtight cabin? ... The second group called my name, a little overwhelmed to the cabin door, immediately saw two people wearing white protective clothing, one with a list check check check, one with a temperature gun, wrist, head to sweep one shot, very serious. I must have been wearing a mask before, but when I got shot in the head, I said, "don't go. Wait by the side. " My heart was racing and my hands were shaking a little.

After a long three minutes, the inspector shot me again, but this time it was normal and said it was time to go. Walking alone across the 23-meter covered bridge, I saw that neither our second group nor our first group of passengers had left the glass vestibule. Outside the door, the lady in dark blue protective clothing was using her mobile phone to constantly direct the airport staff inside to count the number of people, finally, the first 42 people reached the standard, and the door opened. The customs officer who had just checked the names as he stepped off the plane lined everyone up in two lines in the aisle and led us to the inspection hall.

"please scan the code and fill it out online before you enter the interview. " The inspection area is full of people in protective clothing, many of whom have written on the back of their clothes: ex-servicemen, a tribute has been born, you have always been the people's guards, the most lovely people. I was assigned to sit down at the desk of an affable female inspector, who asked me where I had come from, where I had been, personal information, and if I had any uncomfortable symptoms, she looked at the health information registration form number I filled out on the health cloud and motioned for me to be released.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the way to the customs inspection post, I went through several more health form numbers and temperature checks. I was assigned to the Green Channel with no color on my boarding pass, and the yellow and red were estimated to be for observation and emergency personnel, finally I went to the customs passport control, in a few questions after the passport was labeled with a green circle, smoothly out of customs.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the more than 30 hours from San Francisco to Shanghai, from the United States gate to the Chinese gate, the three cities are managed from loose to tight. Shanghai is the strictest and most tender. Just as the most frequently heard words at the airport are: Please understand, it's a responsibility to all of us. The positive change in China's epidemic today is the result of extensive travel restrictions over the past few weeks, and the selfless dedication of the angels in White, in stark contrast to the rest of the world.
